{"actor":{"display":"Evin Tunador","id":"evintunador@gmail.com","type":"human"},"content":{"blocks":[{"content":"1\t---\n2\tname: project-cledger-reanchor-task\n3\tdescription: \"re-anchor shipped in 0.8.0 (four local commits, unpushed as of 2026-07-20); what remains and the design decisions behind it\"\n4\tmetadata: \n5\t  node_type: memory\n6\t  type: project\n7\t  originSessionId: 4c1ed024-2edf-45b6-8cbb-ee40a5ebadc3\n8\t  modified: 2026-07-21T17:35:57.193Z\n9\t---\n10\t\n11\tRe-anchor shipped 2026-07-20 as 0.8.0 in four commits (d3934db, c36b4b5, a452048, 5581e31 — local, not pushed). Originally mis-scoped by a prior session's handoff prompt as post-push purge; purge remains a separate unshipped roadmap item ([[project-cledger-redaction-state]]).\n12\t\n13\tDesign decisions (user-confirmed): append-only `re_anchor` mapping events, never moving notes (union merge would resurrect removals); anchored to the successor commit so mappings ride the surviving DAG; deterministic identity (sorted SHAs, system actor, successor's committer timestamp as occurred_at) so two machines' detections dedup; read-time fixpoint resolution handles chained rewrites; detection = tree equality fast-path + `git patch-id --stable` over -U0 diffs (cumulative for squash, per-commit for rebase), auto-applied on read gated by a target-tip cursor, exact matches only — ambiguity is surfaced, never guessed; `cledger re-anchor` command for dry-run/--apply/manual `--onto` (human actor, GC'd full SHAs accepted verbatim).\n14\t\n15\tSuggestion tier shipped 2026-07-21 as 0.9.0 (commits 61c9c89..8e6bf37, unpushed): forge abstraction in src/forge/ (GitHub driver shells out to the user's `gh` session, 10s timeout, degrades to null — user chose gh over token config), evidence tiers (0: forge merge-commit assertion verified locally; 1: \"(#N)\" subject + squash-message-lists-branch-subjects corroboration; 2: per-file patch-id overlap), confirm-only via printed `--onto` command, forge queried only in the explicit command (auto read path stays offline), `--no-forge`/`{\"reanchor\":{\"forge\":false}}` opt-outs, loud caps (200 candidates, 20 file-scored). Live-tested end to end against real GitHub squash merges on throwaway private repo evintunador/cledger-reanchor-smoke-2026 — **still exists, deletion needs `gh auth refresh -h github.com -s delete_repo` or web UI**. Live testing caught the trim hazard (superseded list is newest-first; user trimming the wrong SHA drops the noted anchor) → output now names conversation-carrying commits.\n16\t\n17\tRemaining/deferred: forge PR-conversation adapter and forge-side CI/App integration (README roadmap items; abstraction now exists to build on); cursor gap (late captures on dead branches only auto-map on next target move) documented in the design doc.\n18\t","tool_use_id":"toolu_01MK3sR2r9Kq96aqGagWYqiM","type":"tool_result"}],"role":"user"},"context":{"branch":"main","cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","dirty_fingerprint":"4b958730eec664173debd21e6aaa53f76db71747f7e61fe3c37269b5ad5d9f2b","head":"d6705ff7ea32c092c92aefdf69cb6a80e7902a24","repo":"git@github.com:evintunador/conversation-ledger.git"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:ca50d7db-8621-495c-a94a-c3d3ab731073","seq":37},"id":"ev1-a9d008f15f0c0898764d802ab2e389db13538d77e8be74b8ab4ef46370477ad7","kind":"conversation_turn","occurred_at":"2026-07-22T17:37:40.449Z","producer":{"session_id":"ca50d7db-8621-495c-a94a-c3d3ab731073","source":"claude-code","tool":"cledger","version":"0.10.0"},"raw":{"data":{"cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","entrypoint":"cli","gitBranch":"main","isSidechain":false,"message":{"content":[{"content":"1\t---\n2\tname: project-cledger-reanchor-task\n3\tdescription: \"re-anchor shipped in 0.8.0 (four local commits, unpushed as of 2026-07-20); what remains and the design decisions behind it\"\n4\tmetadata: \n5\t  node_type: memory\n6\t  type: project\n7\t  originSessionId: 4c1ed024-2edf-45b6-8cb