{"actor":{"display":"Evin Tunador","id":"evintunador@gmail.com","type":"human"},"content":{"blocks":[{"content":"243\t- **Preserve provider-encrypted reasoning as opaque state** *(shipped,\n244\t  0.10.0)* — Codex's `reasoning` response_items carry `encrypted_content`\n245\t  that only OpenAI's servers can decrypt; the client just round-trips the\n246\t  blob, and replaying it restores the model's hidden reasoning\n247\t  provider-side. Capture previously dropped these outright, which conflicted\n248\t  with the record-everything-just-in-case posture: we discarded them because\n249\t  *we* can't read them, yet the one party who can (the provider) already saw\n250\t  the plaintext. Realization (2026-07-21, turnbridge): dropping them\n251\t  permanently forecloses restoring reasoning when a Codex-origin\n252\t  conversation is fabricated back into Codex on another machine (or after a\n253\t  codex→claude→codex round trip). Empirically verified same-account and\n254\t  cross-account (turnbridge `scripts/probe-encrypted-reasoning.mjs`): a real\n255\t  blob replayed in a fabricated session is accepted across sessions, CLI\n256\t  versions, and even a different paid ChatGPT account with identical token\n257\t  accounting — the ciphertext is not keyed per-account. Shipped shape: a new\n258\t  `reasoning` kind, provider-agnostic (not Codex-specific), raw-only —\n259\t  `content` carries only an opacity marker, the blob lives solely in `raw`.\n260\t  Rides the ledger's normal default-on sync like every other kind (no special\n261\t  carve-out). `cledger export` includes it by default (lossless dump);\n262\t  `cledger log`/`show` hide it by default (`--with-reasoning` to reveal) so\n263\t  ciphertext doesn't clutter human-facing transcripts. Forward-only: sessions\n264\t  captured before 0.10.0 already had their reasoning dropped and it's not\n265\t  recovered from what's on disk. *Remaining open questions, mostly\n266\t  turnbridge's to answer at replay time:* blob TTL and A