{"actor":{"display":"Evin Tunador","id":"evintunador@gmail.com","type":"human"},"content":{"blocks":[{"content":[{"text":"## Findings\n\n**1. Real reasoning payloads carry a `summary` field with genuine human-readable plaintext, and it gets swept into the opaque/hidden bucket alongside the ciphertext.**\n\nExtracted every `reasoning` response_item from 37 real rollout files (1,503 items). Every one has the shape `{encrypted_content, id, internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough, summary, type}` — not just `encrypted_content` as the code and its comments assume. `summary` is Codex's live reasoning-summary text (shown to the user in the terminal when `model_reasoning_summary` is enabled) — it is provider-*decrypted*, human-readable content, not ciphertext.\n\n`reasoningDraft` (`src/adapters/drift.ts:93-107`, `content: { opaque: true }` at line 104) and its caller in `src/adapters/codex.ts:358-372` treat the entire response_item as one undifferentiated opaque blob regardless of whether `summary` is populated. `src/schema.ts:18-24`'s doc comment and the whole feature's premise (\"content that should be visible... stays visible, ciphertext hidden by default\") assume reasoning items are pure ciphertext, but that's only true for `encrypted_content` — `summary` is exactly the visible content this feature claims to preserve normally. The result: when a user has reasoning summaries on, real thinking-text the user watched scroll by live gets stored only inside `raw.data`, hidden from `cledger log`/`show` by default (`src/cli.ts:166-172`), and even `--with-reasoning` on `cledger show` (non-JSON path, `src/cli.ts:226-235`) only ever prints `e.content` — literally `{\"opaque\":true}` — never `raw.data`, so the visible summary is unreachable short of `show --json --with-reasoning` or `export`. This directly violates the stated fidelity goal (\"content that should be visible... ends up hidden as opaque\").\n\nThe test suite never catches this: `src/test/adapter-codex.test.ts:50` fixtures a reasoning payload with only `{type, encrypted_content}` — no `summary`, `id`, or `internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough` — so the mismatch between assumed and real payload shape (and the resulting fidelity loss) is untested.\n\n**2. Minor, pre-existing but relevant risk: capture-time redaction walks `raw.data` of `reasoning` events same as everything else.**\n\n`src/store.ts:180-184` runs `redactDraft` (which walks `raw.data`, `src/redact/apply.ts:144-148`) over reasoning drafts before append. Capture-tier regex rules are all anchor-prefixed (`sk-`, `ghp_`, `AKIA`, etc.) so accidental matches inside a base64 `encrypted_content` blob are unlikely, but the \"known-secrets\" exact-substring pass (`redactExtraValues`) would silently splice a `[REDACTED:...]` placeholder into the ciphertext if a previously-remembered secret literal happens to appear as a substring — silently corrupting the blob for replay purposes with no special-case warning, contradicting the \"lossless, record everything\" goal specifically for this opaque-by-design kind. This is a deliberate \"no special carve-out\" design choice per the diff, so flagging as low-severity/edge-case rather than a clear bug.","type":"text"},{"text":"agentId: a0166d8e8bd90f909 (use SendMessage with to: 'a0166d8e8bd90f909', summary: '<5-10 word recap>' to continue this agent)\n<usage>subagent_tokens: 77517\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 196491</usage>","type":"text"}],"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S5FzpEG1gX6AHW8SUHiLw7","type":"tool_result"}],"role":"user"},"context":{"branch":"main","cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","dirty_fingerprint":"7e1b3a10c505480bd4b23ac152d4c1b92e3996d0a55e63b0b41066f69c7d9501","head":"d6705ff7ea32c092c92aefdf69cb6a80e7902a24","repo":"git@github.com:evintunador/conversation-ledger.git"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:ca50d7db-8621-495c-a94a-c3d3ab731073","seq":327},"id":"ev1-4c711da5596be728c2f8c64e40743f1b03599404083bb61f61437427333bddbe","kind":"conversa